The paper deals with problems related to decomposition of graphs into regular, locally regular and/or locally irregular subgraphs, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The algorithms presented in the paper involve graph algorithms (cs.CG) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses lower bounds and upper bounds, which are topics in computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT).
